  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Restore Livelihoods of 100 Rural Farmers in Ogoni</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project supports 100 Ogoni farmers suffering effects of oil polluted lands and rivers through training in alternative livelihoods agriculture on livestock, food crop, and aquaculture production (i.e. poultry, piggery, fishery, snail farming, and mushroom growing) for food support and socio-economic adaptation; and the Centre rehabilitates affected household-farmers in difficulties by transforming their helpless state-of-need to self-supporting status of six-month livelihoods strengthening.</narrative>
  </description>
